title: Grateful Dead Live at Warfield Theater on 1980-10-11
description:
Set 1

Dire Wolf, Dark Hollow, Rosalie McFall, Cassidy, Deep Elem Blues, Monkey & The Engineer, China Doll, Heaven Help The Fool, Ain't No Lie-> Ripple

Set 2

Feel Like A Stranger, They Love Each Other, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Loser, Passenger, Ramble On Rose, Looks Like Rain, Althea, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance

Set 3

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Let It Grow-> Drums-> Not Fade Away*-> Wharf Rat*-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad*-> One More Saturday Night*, E: Brokedown Palace

*W John Cippolina First Set Acoustic

reviews.review_text: Thx Very nice thanks for the upload as always. You guys do a grate job.

Hmmmmm transcending time to the show.... I wish I could review all the shows but, I have to on this one. The Warfield shows are filling the air, and I don't want any new air....but I must progress. I started my bucket list of every show, I think 2yrs ago, and I'm only in 1980.... October.... and it's only getting better. The smooth connect with the backround of being on the stage, develops this show over others. Good morning, how do you do, smile, smile, smile, way back machines, set course to today, then, them, us. Best to beat, not holding my breath, unless it's new air.......
Thank you
